will process, spell processes however work differently.   At set intervals (which are unfortunately unknown) a roll occurs; if the roll is successful a flag is set, and on your next swing it would then process and remove the flag.  When the proc flag is removed, the roll occurs again and you can be re-flagged allowing you to process on both swings of a double attack.<br><br>Interestingly rolls are also done while attack is off, meaning if you buff then don’t attack for a period it’s very likely that you get a process on the first swing.<br><br>From this explanation you should realize that faster weapons do not result in more spell processes.  In the long run you may get a few more processes simply because with a fast weapon you’ll be removing flags faster.  However that will dependant on the delay of the intervals.  (If the delay between rolls is greater than the weapon delay it should make no difference)<br><br>It is possible to have both a weapon, and a spell process on the same swing.<br><br>It was parsed that the change for a spell processes is unchanged by dexterity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufolokthedwarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Folok the Dwarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 9:38:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> :faints with confusion <p><b>Folok Solot</b><BR><i><b>Cavalier of Drinal</i></b><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55557">My Lewts</a><BR><img src="http://rumandmonkey.com/widgets/tests/giantrobot/robocop.jpg" width="200" height="150"><br><a href="http://rumandmonkey.com/widgets/tests/giantrobot/">Which Colossal Death Robot Are <i>You</i>?</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwyrmbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>wyrmbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 10:24:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/oddnfun/wyrmbane_sml.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> <br>Actually, when was the last time you parsed your log on Dex affects?   The reason I ask is that there is a HUGE difference for me when I use Divine Might at my base 107 Dex, and when I have my shaman roommate Cast Harnessing of Spirit, followed by Dexterity giving me a 201 Dexterity.  <br><br>The difference in proc amounts is VERY noticeable.   Hunting in kedge (where I do most of my testing...very safe and easy to control the situation), I get 1, maybe 2 procs during a fight with a Fang pirahna.  With Shaman pet, both of us hasted, we kill it in about 1 minute 30 seconds.  5k hit points on it...and i have a sup-par weapon for my level. <br><br>However, if I have the dex buffs, I can get 4-6 procs in a single fight.   Reading that is does have no effect makes me wonder if I am just seeing things, and it is a perception versus reality issue.<br><br>I will be getting a new weapon and have to train to get it from it's abyssimal average skill to 200.   During that time, I will wipe my log, and do several tests....with and without the =100 Dexterity to check this.....<br><br>wyrmbane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 218<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 10:49:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> On a slightly different vien.<br><br>Divine Might = 65dd proc vs Any<br>Instr. of Nife = 243dd proc vs Undead<br><br>If fighting in a zone with a 50/50 mix of undead and live mobs for an exp camp (Chardok Bridgekeeper area for exmple) which one do you cast? <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>Crusader for Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwallerdaiksar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Waller da Iksar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 10:59:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> I would rather use IoN you would have to have 4 procs of DM to equal one IoN.  So just getting 2 procs per kill on a skelly would make up fer 8 procs of DM on all mobs. <p><p><center><B>-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=119896"><font color="red"><b>Redfish</a></b></font></a>-</B><br><B>-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12575"><font color="GREEN"><font color="purple">The Sentinels of Chaos</a></font></b><br><i>The Tribunal</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uskellt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skellt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 11:15:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Interestingly rolls are also done while attack is off, meaning if you buff then don’t attack for a period it’s very likely that you get a process on the first swing.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Do you people still notice getting a proc on your first swing of a battle if you have had the buff up for a while?  Cuz I keep DM up all the time, and I have never <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>noticed</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that it procs frequently on my first swing.  Is this still true?  Do you still notice this a lot?  Perhaps I'm just not paying attention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uruadinstoutheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruadin Stoutheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.kc.rr.com/matts50l/icon.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 11:17:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> A great compromise in the situation where there is 50/50 live/undead is using boon of the garou from an enchanter.  The proc is meager (35dmg/35hp heal), but it works versus all and most importantly to me it raises attack by 40.  So not only am I doing a small dmg/heal I am getting a higher attack rating...and I don't have to worry about which self proc to use :P<br><br>But really its hard to say which to use of our own.  I always try to use Instrument of Nife whenever able, but it always seems to me as soon as I am geared for undead killing there is a huge streak of live things and it bugs me to not be getting extra damage from the proc I used.  So generally I will use DM since it works versus all.  Besides to me 65dmg versus all is better then nice damage versus undead only, since a lot of spawn situations like that have large streaks of live.<br><br>What really needs to happen is another DM style quest at 60, giving us a minimum of 100dmg proc versus all, preferably around 120dmg  with the 30min duration of IoN.  <br><br>Also even though IoN is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  very</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nice as it is, its a level 30 spell, perhaps we need a upgrade by 60 for that as well...maybe not increase the damage much but maybe the percentage of procs and duration.  Something like 273dmg(Expel undead equiv on proc hehe)/% 10 more proc chance/45 minute duration. Afterall Verant is making us the undead slayers are they not?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Maybe I am wrong about this (since its a very nice dmg addition already), or maybe Verant should have made it a higher level spell, but it seems a class specific level 30 spell should have a upgrade by 60 to me.<br><br>Also another note, I know that dex is not supposed to greatly change proc rates of our spell added procs, but I have also witnessed when I have over 200 dex I will more likely go into &quot;proc frenzy's&quot; as I like to call them where I get upwards of 6 procs in a row.  This never happens with my normal dex around 120's, most that I ever get consecutively without dex buffs seems to be 3 top's, maybe its just a incredible coincidence though.<br><br> <p><B>Ruadin Stoutheart, Crusader of Brell</B><BR></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uruadinstoutheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ruadin Stoutheart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.kc.rr.com/matts50l/icon.JPG" BORDER=0> at: 4/2/02 11:18:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 11:43:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> An unusual thing I noticed while hunting in KC (had IoN up, since I haven't gotten any of the Divine Might pieces yet except the gems) shortly after hitting 49:<br><br>A stupidly high amount of the time, if I waited more than half my weapon's delay (which is 39) to cast Holy Might so that  when I finished casting I would immediately swing, it would very frequently (more than half the time) proc or try to proc IoN on that swing. It even happened twice or three times in a row one fight. Aside from those times, I only rarely procced. (although one time I did 1k damage in the first 2 rounds of combat against an undead MoB... fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But I did also cast Holy Might....) <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Paladin of the 4900th LFG</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaliewin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taliewin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 2:43:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> With something like 120 DEX, I got 7 procs of IoN in one fight once (unfortunately one only hit for 29dam <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), against the Ghoul Lord.  With the same DEX I have gone through two whole fights without a proc (though unusual).  <br><br>Due to gear changes my DEX is now something like 103, and the reduction I have seen in procs (based on observation, not parsing) is small, though I have still noticed it. I was getting on average I would say nearly two procs per fight, whereas now it would be closer to one (vs. LGuk Frogloks).<br><br> <p><img src="http://www.boomspeed.com/taliewin/TaliewinLifesworde.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uluthair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Luthair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 1819<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 2:48:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> Taliewin, even with a weapon proc you wouldn't see that much of a decrease in procs with only lowering dex by 20.<br><br>I've seen parses that only show that +70 dex only increases your total number of spell procs by ~20%. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalantia>Dalantia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 6:29:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proc Buffs (Divine Might, Instrument of Nife, etc)</span><hr size=1> I had a Giant Militia Tunic (25 AC -20 Dex) that I dropped because I usually use IoN to fight.  I noticed that my proc rate went WAY down when my dex fell below 75 (resulting dex was 73).<br><br>Just an opinion. *grins* <p>Dalantia Dragonet<br>Aiyeka's Beloved Guardian, 44th Rank<br>Fennin Ro<br>Unguilded</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=15136.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=15136.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15136.topic&index=10><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=15136.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/e